    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe following file is misdetected as `diff`, breaking <https://github.com/tpope/vim-fugitive>'s blame syntax highlighting:\n```\n0d555557  1 (John John   2025-01-01 00:00:00 +0000  1) foo\n```\nChanging the sha to `0e555557` makes it work correctly.\n\nI believe this is because the regex in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/36361d6e4a189e0d53a26bdaa8d9aa5db791b6d7/runtime/lua/vim/filetype/detect.lua#L2073 catches any git sha that has exactly one letter `c`, `d` or `a` and no other letters.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\necho '0d555557  1 (John John   2025-01-01 00:00:00 +0000  1) foo' >x1\necho '0e555557  1 (John John   2025-01-01 00:00:00 +0000  1) foo' >x2\nvim -u NONE x1\n:syntax on\n:echo &ft\nvim -u NONE x2\n:syntax on\n:echo &ft\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe first echo shouldn't say \"diff\".\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.1.1230\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nn/a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nn/a",
